# Design Rules

## Visual language

- Follow **retro-modern OS UI + editorial layout** from `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`.
- Page background: off-white (`bg-canvas` / `#F2F2F2`). Primary borders: 1px black/near-black.
- Accents: muted lavender-blue (`accent` / `#7B8CDE`) — not bright royal blue or purple gradients.
- Motifs (globe, barcode, star, OS window) are **decorative**. They must not compete with headlines or CTAs.

## Typography

- **Display/pixel font:** Hero name only.
- **Body:** Sans-serif. **Labels/nav/badges:** Monospace uppercase.
- Section labels: ALL CAPS, mono, letter-spaced — e.g. `FEATURED PROJECTS`.
- Max prose width ~65ch on about and case studies.

## Components

- Build from `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` component inventory before one-off markup.
- Buttons: primary (black fill), secondary (white + border). Never icon-only without `aria-label`.
- Project cards use variants: `dark-globe`, `blue-cube`, `light-browser`, `light-wave`.
- Shadows: avoid unless necessary; prefer borders.

## Responsive & motion

- Mobile-first Tailwind. Test at 375px before marking UI complete.
- Hero stacks on mobile (copy first, visual second).
- Transitions ≤ 300ms. Honor `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- No parallax, scroll-jacking, or cursor effects.

## Tailwind tokens

- Use semantic tokens (`bg-canvas`, `text-ink`, `border-ink`, `accent`) — not raw hex in components except `global.css` `@theme`.
- Tailwind v4 is CSS-first via `@theme` in `src/styles/global.css`. No `tailwind.config.js`.
